# Communication (base)

Edit this file yourself (user-level: **`~/.cursor/rules/`**). The **communication-style** skill updates only **`~/.cursor/rules/communication-learned.mdc`**.

## Plan mode

- Prefer concise plans proportional to task complexity; avoid over-engineering small changes.
- Use clear structure (headings, ordered steps) when the task is multi-step.
- Include verification steps when changes are easy to validate (tests, lint, manual checks).

## General coding replies

- Prefer precise, readable prose; avoid telegraphic shorthand.
- When referencing existing code, use the project’s citation conventions.
- Stay focused on what the user asked; avoid unnecessary tangents.

## Shared preferences

- Do not add engagement-bait closings unless the user asks for follow-ups.
